{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771579871,"nonce":"Q6lYIGGXXvmJgKw4Mcwf2p2gEfc=","title":"Retain conduct records when bans are lifted instead of deleting","message":"When a ban is lifted via remove_conduct, the conduct record is destroyed. This loses historical information that is valuable for department administrators - knowing a borrower was previously banned helps assess behavior patterns and decide on future bans.\n\nProposed approach:\n- Add a status field to conducts (e.g. active/lifted) instead of destroying records\n- remove_conduct should set status to lifted (with timestamp and who lifted it) rather than destroy\n- has_bans_here?, has_bans_in? and similar queries should only consider active conducts\n- The unique ban index (borrower_id + department_id WHERE kind=1) needs to also filter on active status\n- The borrower detail view should show lifted bans differently (greyed out, crossed out, or in a separate history section)\n- Ban lifted email should still be sent\n\nFound during Phase C integration testing.","files":null}]}